I went down to the local police station the other day to report a crime: a serial armed robbery. The constable looked perplexed when I said the robbery hasn’t occurred yet, and would take place sometime between tomorrow and the end of the year. I tried to explain as best I could. By all accounts, a villain named Tito Mboweni will tomorrow, armed with a budget speech, announce that millions of South Africans will be robbed of their hard-earned money to finance a criminal gang going by the name of the ANC. “Huh?” said the constable. “Armed with a speech?”...